Y16 IsPositive

Given Number N, print Positive if it is positive number. Print Negative if it is Negative number.

Input Format

Single value represents N.

Constraints

-10,00,000 <= N <= 10,00,000

Output Format

Single word represents either Positive or Negative

Sample Input 0

1
Sample Output 0

Positive
Sample Input 1

0
Sample Output 1

Positive


Solution:
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner ik=new Scanner(System.in);
        int k=ik.nextInt();
        if(k>=0)
        {
            System.out.println("Positive");
        }
        else
        {
                System.out.println("Negative"); 
        }
    }
}
